public class IRuntime
extends INoCopy
    \class IRuntime \brief Allows a serialized functionally unsafe engine to be deserialized. \warning Do not inherit from this class, as doing so will break forward-compatibility of the API and ABI.

      • deserializeCudaEngine

        @Deprecated
 @NoException(value=true)
public ICudaEngine deserializeCudaEngine(@Const
                                                                                 Pointer blob,
                                                                                 @Cast(value="std::size_t")
                                                                                 long size,
                                                                                 IPluginFactory pluginFactory)
        Deprecated. Deprecated interface will be removed in TensorRT 10.0. \warning IPluginFactory is no longer supported, therefore pluginFactory must be a nullptr.
        \brief Deserialize an engine from a stream. If an error recorder has been set for the runtime, it will also be passed to the engine.
        Parameters:
        blob - The memory that holds the serialized engine.
        size - The size of the memory in bytes.
        pluginFactory - The plugin factory, if any plugins are used by the network, otherwise nullptr.
        Returns:
        The engine, or nullptr if it could not be deserialized.

      • setDLACore

        @NoException(value=true)
public void setDLACore(int dlaCore)
        \brief Set the DLA core that the deserialized engine must execute on.
        Parameters:
        dlaCore - The DLA core to execute the engine on (0 to N-1, where N is the maximum number of DLA's present on the device). Default value is 0. @see getDLACore() \warning Starting with TensorRT 8, the default value will be -1 if the DLA is not specified or unused.

      • getDLACore

        @NoException(value=true)
public int getDLACore()
        \brief Get the DLA core that the engine executes on.
        Returns:
        If setDLACore is called, returns DLA core from 0 to N-1, else returns 0. \warning Starting with TensorRT 8, the default value will be -1 if the DLA is not specified or unused.

      • setGpuAllocator

        @NoException(value=true)
public void setGpuAllocator(IGpuAllocator allocator)
        \brief Set the GPU allocator.
        Parameters:
        allocator - Set the GPU allocator to be used by the runtime. All GPU memory acquired will use this allocator. If NULL is passed, the default allocator will be used. Default: uses cudaMalloc/cudaFree. If nullptr is passed, the default allocator will be used.
